data.description: Charming & Historic! this magnificent 5 bedroom, 2 bath home built in 1927 is a rare gem that exudes timeless elegance and character. Behold the classic architecture!  As you step through the front door, you are greeted by a warm and inviting living room with rich hardwood floors, original moldings, and a cozy fireplace that provides a perfect gathering spot. The spacious dining room with large windows, is perfect for hosting formal dinners or intimate gatherings.  The chef's kitchen has maintained its vintage charm and features ample storage, and a cozy breakfast nook that overlooks the backyard.  The main floor also features two bedrooms and 1 bathroom. Upstairs, you'll find three additional bedrooms, including a luxurious primary suite with a large walk-in closet.  The basement provides for additional living space, storage or whatever your heart desires . The home is also equipped with a detached garage and driveway that provides ample off-street parking.Located in a desirable and well-established Boise neighborhood, this home is just minutes away from trendy shops, restaurants, and parks. Don't miss out on the opportunity to own a piece of Portland's history while enjoying all the lifestyle you can handle. [Home Energy Score = 1. HES Report at https://rpt.greenbuildingregistry.com/hes/OR10199258]
